    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"816344\">Aaron Liu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Need.20help.20defining.20an.20instance/near/536694130\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=PolynomialModule#doc\">docs#PolynomialModule</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I am aware of this but I don't see how it helps. Of course, I have a module structure on <code>PolynomialModule R (MvPolynomial (Fin n) R)</code>, which is mathematically the same but isn't an instance I'm looking for.</p>",
